column5: None. In fact, I didn't last long at that job because I was there to help rehabilitate people not punish them like the rest of the staff I worked with.

I know this sounds crazy, but I seriously thought I was the only one with this kind of suffering as I watched the ball drop last night. I live on the 21st floor of a 27 floor apartment building and the only reason I didn't jump was because I wasn't sure if it would kill me.
